<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 1:41PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central
Garfield and eastern Iron Counties through 215 PM MDT...
At 140 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Panguitch Lake, or 24 miles east of Cedar City, moving north at 5
mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Panguitch Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
